	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>. <date>July 13&#44; 1854</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Respected friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I have received another<lb/> case of your books&#44; and have expected<lb/> according to promise to hear from<lb/> you in reference to their disposal&#44;<lb/> you will therefore please write<lb/> me by return of mail what you<lb/> want done with them&#44; how many<lb/> you want me to send to Provid&#45;<lb/>dence&#44; and to what parties.  I<lb/> have also in hands &#36;10.00 from<lb/> <persName>Mr. Kingsbury</persName> for his bible&#44; and<lb/> &#36;14.00 from <persName>Mr. Bornstien</persName> for a<lb/> bible &#40;8.00&#41; and 2 years subscription<lb/> &#40;6.00&#41; to the &#8220;Occident.&#8221;  You will also please<lb/> credit me with &#36;1.62 for freight<lb/> for the cases.  Hoping to hear from<lb/> you by return of mail.</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">I remain respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Your <sic>freind</sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Spier</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. If you wish I will send you what<lb/> money I have on hand by express.</p>
		</body>
